description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and enthusiastic radiographer to join our friendly imaging team. We have the full compliment of imaging modalities (MRI, CT, US, NM, Mammography, fluorscopy, theatre work, and dedicated orthopaedic centre) with digital imaging in all areas .&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are committed to staff development and post graduate training throughout the range of modalities on site and have staff rotations to other sites within the health board to ensure access to all modalities. An active audit/teaching programme is supported and the department also provides clinical placements for under graduate students. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The hospital is situated 5 minutes drive from Cardiff Bay and 10 minutes from Cardiff City centre. Both have a young and vibrant nightlife with a range of restaurants and clubs. The hospital is also well positioned for access to the Gower Peninsular with its award winning beaches and the Brecon Beacons National park.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peter Smith&lt;/p&gt;
